# Codex Bootstrap default rules

- Prefer the configured custom provider for gateway-backed Codex usage.
- Never print full API keys, tokens, session cookies, or private env file contents.
- Use subagents for long-running exploration, repository scans, and verification when available.
- Prefer small, reversible changes with backups before modifying user-level Codex configuration.
- Keep project-specific instructions in AGENTS.md and global behavioral defaults in ~/.codex/rules/default.rules.
- Treat danger-full-access as a productivity mode, not a reason to skip path checks, tests, or user-change protection.
- After meaningful edits, run the narrowest available verification before reporting success.
